  "2026-05-25T12:28:13.524Z",codex-reliability-history-agent,"Execution update 2026-05-25 for combined reliability/history PR slice (single-agent, no duplicates):\n\n- Orientation + dedupe evidence rerun: pm context --limit 10; pm search \"reliability history windows dependabot changelog pm-7rlp pm-xk39\" --limit 10; pm list-open --limit 20 --brief; pm list-in-progress --limit 20 --brief. Reused canonical active lineage pm-7rlp + pm-xk39 under pm-rnpb.\n- Claim/bootstrap evidence: bootstrap completed per AGENTS.md (npm install -g ., pm --version, node -v, pnpm -v, pnpm build), PM_AUTHOR set to codex-reliability-history-agent, and item claim ownership moved to this run.\n- Workflow reliability fix: updated .github/workflows/release.yml softprops/action-gh-release pin to current v3.0.0 commit b4309332981a82ec1c5618f44dd2e27cc8bfbfda and aligned tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts.\n- In-process parity enhancement: extended tests/integration/cli-inprocess-runner.integration.spec.ts with concurrent Promise.all in-process runs + process-global restoration checks (cwd/env isolation) while preserving existing subprocess parity assertions.\n- GitHub run triage via gh: no open issues/PRs; no open Dependabot alerts; no open secret-scanning alerts. Historical failures examined from gh run view logs: stale release action SHA/Dependabot softprops no-such-commit and prior nightly Windows regression signatures.\n- Focused verification passed:\n  - node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts\n  - node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts tests/unit/package-manifest.spec.ts tests/unit/check-secrets.spec.ts tests/integration/release-automation-contract.spec.ts --reporter=dot (101 tests)\n  - node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/cli-inprocess-runner.integration.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts -t 'keeps subprocess and in-process runner behavior aligned for core flows|keeps concurrent in-process runs isolated and restores globals|keeps Sentry startup lazy for fast CLI commands' --reporter=dot\n- Full release gate passed on this change set: node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --telemetry-mode required --max-sentry-critical 10 --max-sentry-high 20 --max-telemetry-error-rate 10 --json (1770 tests, 100% coverage, static/docs/security/npx/dogfood/compatibility and sentry-telemetry gate all ok)."
  "2026-05-25T12:47:13.642Z",codex-reliability-history-agent,"AI feedback follow-up on PR #68: refined in-process concurrency parity test to avoid unmanaged global env mutation patterns, snapshot/restore sentinel env state in finally, and assert process.argv restoration in addition to cwd restoration. Re-ran targeted parity/startup regressions; all passing."
  "2026-05-25T19:47:35.952Z",codex-full-audit,"CI/test performance findings from this pass: static quality gate is green and focused tests pass, but the suite still overuses subprocess CLI calls (sub-agent counted ~815 runCli uses vs 4 runCliInProcess uses) and full coverage remains gated by a high-friction manifest/allowlist. Local package-first dogfood passed, with slowest operations roughly 1.0-2.1s in temp projects. I added focused regression tests rather than broad slow integration coverage: help-runtime error recovery, calendar package validation, package manifest capability/export checks, LanceDB snapshot cache invalidation, and SDK core-command boundary assertions. Remaining work for this item should migrate high-volume integration clusters to in-process runner and dedupe release/auto-release workflow gates."
  "2026-05-25T19:53:04.737Z",codex-gh-ci-dependency-triage,"Read-only GitHub/CI/dependency triage 2026-05-25:\n\nScope honored: no source/workflow/package edits; only tracker evidence appended. Started from pm-rnpb and pm-7rlp, then checked current open items. Reused pm-7rlp for CI/test findings; no duplicate item created.\n\nGitHub state:\n- gh issue list --state open --limit 50 --json ... => [] (no open issues).\n- gh pr list --state open --limit 50 --json ... => [] (no open PRs).\n- gh run list --limit 20 --json ... => latest main CI run 26416020351 on f47901c completed success; previous main run 26415948706 was cancelled by concurrency after newer push.\n- gh api repos/:owner/:repo/dependabot/alerts => all returned alerts are state=fixed; no open Dependabot security alert found.\n- gh api repos/:owner/:repo/secret-scanning/alerts => [] (no secret-scanning alerts returned).\n- pnpm audit --audit-level moderate --json => 0 low/moderate/high/critical vulnerabilities across 281 total dependencies.\n- gh api repos/:owner/:repo/code-scanning/alerts could not be used in this token/session: API reported no analysis found and requested admin:repo_hook scope. Treat code-scanning as not verified by this pass.\n\nCI/workflow findings:\n- ci.yml current topology matches pm-7rlp direction: build-foundation on Ubuntu Node 20, runtime smoke matrix, and gates matrix for coverage/typecheck/static/compat/smokes. No duplicate full pnpm test in PR/push runtime matrix observed.\n- Auto Release recent scheduled failures 26353906615 and 26387640606 are already covered by closed pm-yf8t. Logs show dist/cli.js MODULE_NOT_FOUND before the build step existed. Current main has ae3d884e adding Build before Run auto release pipeline, so this pass did not reopen it; next scheduled run should be watched for confirmation.\n- Nightly Validation is still red and maps to this item: latest run 26390994985 failed only on windows-latest Node 20; ubuntu Node 20/22/24/25 and macOS Node 20 jobs passed. Windows failures: tests/unit/check-secrets.spec.ts suite SyntaxError, tests/integration/release-automation-contract.spec.ts SyntaxError in tracker-only release relevance test, tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts spawnSync npm ENOENT at npm pack, and tests/unit/package-manifest.spec.ts generated runtime loader drift for pm-beads/pm-todos on Windows. This confirms cross-platform nightly remains the active CI follow-up under pm-7rlp.\n\nDependency/update notes:\n- dependabot.yml is present for npm and github-actions weekly Monday 04:00 UTC, grouped minor/patch updates, open PR limit 5.\n- gh pr list currently shows no open Dependabot PRs, but remote refs still include historical dependabot branches; no action needed without an open PR.\n\nCommands/evidence used include: git status --short --branch; pm get pm-rnpb --json; pm get pm-7rlp --json; pm list-open --json; gh auth status; gh repo view --json nameWithOwner,defaultBranchRef,isPrivate,url,latestRelease,securityPolicyUrl,pushedAt,viewerPermission; gh issue list; gh pr list; gh run list; gh run view 26387640606 --json/--log-failed; gh run view 26390994985 --json/--log-failed; gh api dependabot/alerts; gh api secret-scanning/alerts; gh api dependency-graph/sbom; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate --json; sed over .github workflows and dependabot.yml; package.json script inspection.\n"
  "2026-05-25T20:08:30.929Z",codex-code-quality-specialist,"Code-quality specialist evidence 2026-05-25: bounded gates mostly pass but CI/test performance and coverage are not healthy. Commands: pnpm typecheck passed elapsed=4.211s; node scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs --json passed elapsed=2.600s; pnpm quality:docs-skills passed elapsed=10.270s; node scripts/check-secrets.mjs passed elapsed=1.263s; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- --reporter=dot passed 121 files / 1804 tests elapsed=284.904s. Full serial coverage command PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage -- --reporter=dot --testTimeout 120000 --maxWorkers 1 failed after elapsed=652.964s: Vitest reported coverage/.tmp disappeared, and coverage-summary.json shows total lines 99.87, statements 99.88, branches 99.72 with src/core/search/vector-stores.ts below 100%. Recommended fix: add focused coverage for current LanceDB cache branches in vector-stores.ts, then rerun coverage; also make run-tests/coverage use an isolated reportsDirectory or preflight lock/cleanup so long coverage runs cannot collide with stale or concurrent coverage state."
  "2026-05-25T20:14:23.440Z",codex-full-audit,"Final verification 2026-05-25: CI/test quality gate restored after vector-store coverage regression. Full release gate passed with 121 files / 1806 tests / 100% coverage. Remaining performance work stays open: sub-agent evidence shows most wall time is bootstrap/module/extension loading and high-volume integration tests still overuse subprocess runCli compared with runCliInProcess."
  "2026-05-25T20:19:46.311Z",ci-quality-subagent,"CI/test quality sub-agent start 2026-05-25: ran pm context/search/list-open/list-in-progress; reusing pm-7rlp for CI/test performance and pm-3cbk for large-module/coverage maintainability. Scope: inspect latest dirty checkout, package scripts, Vitest config, CLI runner usage, current diff, and focused quality gates without reverting others' work."
  "2026-05-25T20:23:34.500Z",ci-quality-subagent,"CI/test quality sub-agent final evidence 2026-05-25: inspected package scripts, vitest.config.ts, tests/helpers/cliRunner.ts, tests/helpers/withTempPmPath.ts, scripts/run-tests.mjs, .github/workflows/ci.yml, .github/workflows/nightly.yml, current diff, GitHub open PR/issues/runs, dependency audit, and runCli usage. Findings: CI topology already uses the right dedupe shape for PR/push (build-foundation, runtime dist smoke matrix, coverage/typecheck/static/compat/smokes gates) and nightly keeps full OS/Node breadth; no open PRs or issues; latest main CI run 26416020351 completed success; pnpm audit found no known vulnerabilities. Remaining performance issue is test-suite subprocess overuse: 822 context.runCli calls vs 4 runCliInProcess calls and 6 direct dist helper calls, so pm-7rlp should stay open for broad migration of high-volume integration specs. Local verification from this pass: pnpm typecheck PASS 6.271s before helper edit and PASS 11.024s after helper edit; static-quality-gate PASS 4.722s; check-secrets PASS 1.817s; focused changed-surface test command PASS 9 files / 129 tests / 30 skipped in 58.812s; stdin append focused command PASS 1 file / 5 tests / 9 skipped in 21.521s. I made one scoped test-helper type fix: tests/helpers/withTempPmPath.ts now includes input in the runCli closure options so it matches TempPmContext and the subprocess runner contract. I did not rerun full coverage because codex-full-audit had just recorded full release gate success with 1806 tests and 100% coverage after the vector-store fix, and this pass only added tracker evidence plus a helper typing fix covered by typecheck/focused stdin tests."
  "2026-05-25T20:25:22.810Z",manual-dogfood-subagent,"Manual linked-test evidence: initial test add with command=npm test was rejected by sandbox safety until both PM_PATH and PM_GLOBAL_PATH were explicit; after adding explicit env and making the temp test emit expected stdout, pm test --run passed in 1739ms and pm test-all passed in 1697ms with linked_tests=1 passed=1 failed=0. This confirms safety guardrails work, but test commands are still subprocess-bound and around 1.7s for a tiny node smoke."
  "2026-05-25T20:28:24.347Z",observability-security-subagent,"CI/automation evidence from observability-security subagent 2026-05-25: latest main CI run 26416020351 succeeded for commit f47901c with all jobs green. Historical same-day failures reviewed for context: Auto Release 26387640606 failed because release pipeline ran before dist existed; current auto-release workflow now includes `pnpm build` before `node scripts/release/run-release-pipeline.mjs`. Nightly 26390994985 failed only on Windows Node 20 with npm spawn/runtime-loader sync/syntax failures; later main CI is green. CI 26397135725 failed static gate in changelog extension handling; later main CI static gate succeeded. Dependabot update 26384310873 failed in upstream updater for an action update and left no open alert. No new CI source edits made by this subagent.\n"
  "2026-05-25T20:37:01.129Z",github-dependency-security-scout,"CI-specific GitHub scout evidence 2026-05-25 (read-only aside from tracker comment): latest main CI run 26416020351 succeeded for f47901c. Recent failed runs reviewed with gh run view/logs: CI 26397135725 failed Gates(static) in changelog generate extension handler, then later main CI went green; Nightly 26390994985 failed only Windows Node 20 with check-secrets/release-relevance SyntaxError, spawnSync npm ENOENT in packed extension test, and generated runtime-loader drift; Auto Release 26387640606 failed before build existed with Cannot find module dist/cli.js, matching the now-addressed build-before-release-pipeline fix; Dependabot Updates 26384310873 failed in upstream updater on softprops/action-gh-release unknown_error, while setup-node/upload-artifact were already latest. Blocker assessment for current PR: do not block on these historical failures because latest main CI is green and no open PR/check is red; keep pm-7rlp open for the Windows/runner and subprocess-portability performance work if not already fully resolved.\n"
  "2026-05-26T15:43:42.628Z",claude-code-agent,"Execution start 2026-05-26: claiming pm-7rlp for nightly cross-platform stability slice. Two real failures in last nightly (26439727168): (1) tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts:756 macOS realpath mismatch (/var/folders vs /private/var/folders), (2) tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts:234 Windows spawnSync npm.cmd EINVAL (Node 20 CVE-2024-27980 hardening still requires shell:true even with .cmd suffix). Combining with pm-3cbk dedup follow-up: extract buildExtensionPolicyOverride helper to remove 25-line duplicate between normalizeExtensionPolicy and hydrateExtensionPolicy. Branch fix/nightly-cross-platform-stability-and-extension-policy-dedup."
  "2026-05-26T15:53:37.292Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation evidence 2026-05-26: applied two surgical nightly fixes on branch fix/nightly-cross-platform-stability-and-extension-policy-dedup. (1) tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts:234 added shell:true on Windows for execFileSync(npm.cmd) to satisfy Node CVE-2024-27980 hardening (.cmd files now require shell mode); (2) tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts:729 wrapped mkdtemp(os.tmpdir()) in await realpath(...) so macOS resolves /var/folders -> /private/var/folders before comparing with resolveInstallSource output (the production code path already realpaths via underlying fs.realpath). Verification: targeted tests pass (extension-command + cli.integration), extension-loader/settings-store/settings-validator/contracts-command (90 tests) pass after the extension-policy override extraction. Full release gate node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --telemetry-mode best-effort --json reports ok=true across build/typecheck/docs/static/coverage/version/secrets/npx-smoke/package-first-dogfood/npm-pack/compat/sentry-telemetry; coverage at 100% statements/branches/functions/lines; Sentry critical=0, high=5 (within threshold), telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=1.95, missing-error-code rows=0. Manual temp-dir dogfood verified init/create/list/search/context/health/validate happy path with the new extension-policy override path traversed."
  "2026-05-26T16:22:58.486Z",claude-code-agent,"Slice merged 2026-05-26 via PR #73 (commit 60659285). Closed pm-gf6f covers the macOS realpath + Windows .cmd EINVAL fixes. pm-7rlp remains in_progress for the broader CI/test perf work: in-process runner adoption expansion across release-readiness-runtime and cli.integration specs, remaining matrix dedup beyond the runtime-smoke layer."
